  <h2><i class="fa fa-hand-o-right"></i> Overview</h2>

  <p>Engines is for running servers. Use it to self-host server software and store data. Create a cloud environment that you own and control.</p>

  <h3>Flexible</h3>
  <p>You can install Engines on a computer in the office or at home, or on a virtual machine hosted in the cloud. Find a range of software in the offical Engines library as well as third-party libraries.</p>

  <h3>Easy</h3>
  <p>Engines provides an easy-to-use interface to manage your system and its software. Applications are straightforward to install, configure and maintain. Back-ups are simple to set-up and run.</p>

  <h3>Share</h3>
  <p>Connect files and data between applications, to your devices, and to friends and colleagues.</p>

  <h3>Security</h3>
  <p>Only you hold the keys to your system and logs. Applications run in sandboxed containers to protect your server from malicious and defective software.</p>

  <h3>Privacy</h3>
  <p>Have sovereignty over your data. Domicile in the jurisdiction that makes most sense for you. Run a VPN for extra protection.</p>

  <h3>Software</h3>
  <p>Use Engines for blogging, instant messaging, media libraries, social networking, multiplayer gaming, online stores, managing projects, CRM, fleet tracking, voip, accounting, document sharing, group contacts and calendar, ERP, education platform servers, email and more.</p>

